canonical:
  title: 崔弘義讓金吾衛上將軍攝刑部尙書不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 神考君臨宇內十有八年內有奠枕之安外無羽檄之警德業之盛超軼今古苟非文臣武士協心戮力何以臻此卿嚮自先朝乃至今日出而捍禦于外入而宿衛于內歲月滋久厥功茂焉是用授上將之秩加八座之聯爵位旣高責任又重往求自稱惟懋忠勤毋或多言朕命不易
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 崔弘義讓金吾衛上將軍攝刑部尙書不允
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 神考君臨宇內。十有八年。內有奠枕之安。外無羽檄之警。德業之盛。超軼今古。苟非文臣武士協心戮力。何以臻此。卿嚮自先朝。乃至今日。出而捍禦于外。入而宿衛于內。歲月滋久。厥功茂焉。是用授上將之秩。加八座之聯。爵位旣高。責任又重。往求自稱。惟懋忠勤。毋或多言。朕命不易。
korean:
  title: 최홍의 양 금오위 상장군 섭 형부상서 불윤
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: 선고께서 이 나라에 군림하신 지 18년 동안 국내가 태평하였고, 국경엔 전쟁의 경보가 없었으며, 왕업의 융성함이 고금에 으뜸이었는데, 참으로 문신과 무사들이 온 마음을 다해 협력하지 않았다면 어찌 이러한 성과를 이루었겠는가.경은 선조 때부터 오늘날에 이르도록, 나가서는 외방에서 외적을 막아내고 들어와서는 궁중을 숙위하여, 오랜 세월 동안 크나큰 공을 세웠다. 그러므로 이제 상장군의 벼슬을 주고 겸하여 상서(尙書)의 반열에 올렸다. 작위가 이미 높으매 책임이 또한 중하니, 가서 직책을 다하고 오직 충근(忠勤)을 힘쓸지어다. 여러 말을 하지 말라. 짐의 명령은 바꿀 수가 없다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0230&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Imperial Decree Denying Choi Hong-ui's Request to Decline the Position of Commander of the Gold Hawk Guard and Acting Minister of Justice
  author: Anonymous
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Our Divine Sovereign has ruled this realm for eighteen years. Within, our people rest in tranquility; without, no war drums sound upon our borders. The splendor of Our state surpasses all ages past and present—yet this could never have been achieved had not Our civil and military officials joined their hearts and exerted their utmost strength together.

    You, since the reign of Our predecessor until this very day, have ventured forth to defend Our frontiers against enemies, and returned to stand guard within Our palace. Through long years of service, you have amassed great merit. Therefore, We bestow upon you the rank of Grand General and elevate you to the ranks of the Three High Officials, assuming also the office of Minister of Justice.

    Your position is now exalted, and your responsibilities are weighty. Go forth and fulfill your duties with steadfast devotion. Show Us only your unwavering loyalty and diligence. Speak no further against this appointment. Our imperial word is immutable.
  footnotes:
    - This is an imperial rescript refusing a court official's petition to decline a high office, a common literary form in East Asian official records.
    - The 'Divine Sovereign' (神考) refers to the reigning king; the reference to eighteen years of rule provides historical context for dating this document.
    - The 'Three High Officials' (八座) or Eight Ranks refer to the highest ministerial positions in the Confucian bureaucratic system.
